bug.description:
Version 0.9.0.
The actual problem is that the connection to the streaming port fails (and the failure message is debug only). Somehow using the tcp endpoint as given only works on Linux. I've tried using a resolver instead and seems to work.
boost::asio::ip::tcp::resolver resolver(_socket.get_io_service());
auto endpoint_it = resolver.resolve({"127.0.0.1", "2001"});
boost::asio::async_connect(_socket, endpoint_it, _strand.wrap(handle_connect));
